00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Your best ideas don't wait for you to sit down.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:08.000
They arrive on a walk. Between meetings. While you're holding something else in your head.

00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:12.700
The question isn't where they come from — it's whether you can catch them before they slip.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.200
That's what Talkie is for. Three principles.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:18.300
Velocity.

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:21.500
Your voice is the fastest path from thought to action.

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:27.500
Speak it, and it lands — in your draft, your task list, your terminal, wherever you were already going.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:29.500
Sovereignty.

00:00:29.700 --> 00:00:32.000
Your words stay on your devices.

00:00:32.300 --> 00:00:38.500
We don't ship them to a cloud to be useful. The signal path is short, and it's yours.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Flow.

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:44.500
The cursor returns to where it started. Your hands stay where they were.

00:00:44.700 --> 00:00:47.500
Talkie doesn't ask you to leave what you're doing.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.300
Your voice is the fastest path.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:53.300
Don't let the tools slow you down.
